1.title: We See You, Kelsey Smith
1.plot: A teenage girl disappears from a Kansas Mall. The only clue for detectives - the haunting final images of her on surveillance video. Somewhere in these frames hides the answer - and a killer....

2.title: View to a Rampage
2.plot: A couple, just engaged, is found brutally murdered in a car. To investigators it looks like an execution. No leads until a surveillance camera 90 miles away gives the investigation its first break - a killer bent on revenge. It's a race against time.

3.title: Neighborhood Watch
3.plot: Pensacola, FL.- two murders, one witness:Police investigate the strange disappearance of a reporter and exposed to an addictive world of gaming.Across state a mom vanishes after a party. Detectives have no leads until cameras begin to spill their secrets.

4.title: Silent Witness
4.plot: A husband and respected businessman vanishes after a meeting. Meanwhile a young mother doesn't come back from her job search. Cops can only rely on one witness-one that never lies-surveillance cameras.

5.title: Mansion Murder Cam
5.plot: In Pensacola Florida, two loving parents are brutally gunned down in their own home. The cop's only witness one that never lies surveillance cameras. It's what they must rely on, to catch the killers and bring them to justice.

6.title: What Happened to Skylar Neese?
6.plot: Every parent's worst nightmare comes true when a schoolgirl disappears without a trace. But a few seconds of surveillance footage leads cops to the most shocking discovery imaginable.

1.title: Watching Amy Lord
1.plot: After 24-year-old Amy Lord is found stabbed to death, police trace her movements using footage from five different ATMs in Boston.

2.title: Good Samaritan
2.plot: Bright young college student Kenia Monge disappears without a trace. The family's search for their 19-year-old daughter hits every dead end... until detectives uncover chilling surveillance footage, revealing exactly what happened to her.

3.title: Must Find Mickey
3.plot: 21-year-old Mickey Shunick is missing after a night out. Her family is terrified and mobilizes the local community to help search for her. Police are unable to find any trace of the Louisiana student -- until they spot her on surveillance video...

4.title: The Vanishing Nurse
4.plot: Bright young nursing student Michelle Le vanishes without a trace. An old friend of hers points a finger at Michelle's ex-boyfriend. Cops discover footage that shows Michelle's car driving around the parking lot where she vanished, but who is the driver?

5.title: Watching Dru
5.plot: Young student Dru Sjodin suddenly vanishes after her shift at Victoria's Secret. Investigators turn to the best eyewitness they have: surveillance camera footage. Dru's last movements are traced and reveal the chilling reason for her disappearance.

6.title: Vanished from Campus
6.plot: A young man goes missing. His girlfriend and best friend help the authorities find clues to his location. Suspense and shock erupts as they go on this journey.

7.title: Driven to the Edge
7.plot: After dropping her two boys at school in Coral Springs, Florida, Surya Toha vanishes without a trace. Her husband is devastated and detectives have few clues to work with... until chilling CCTV footage reveals exactly what happened to her.

8.title: The Vanishing Babysitter
8.plot: When 15 year old Elizabeth Ennen doesn't return home from a babysitting job one evening the family and police are leaving left to figure out what has happened to the teenage girl.

9.title: Snatched on Camera
9.plot: 19-year-old college student Katie Poirier vanishes while working the graveyard shift at a gas station. It's a family's worst nightmare come true. Grainy security footage reveals an answer... but leaves a community in fear.

10.title: Mr. Reed Will See You
10.plot: Keith Reed is found gunned down on his doorstep. What seems like a possible crime of passion is turned on its head after a surprise discovery. Surveillance footage helps police unravel the mystery behind Keith's death and just who killed him.

11.title: One Chance, One Look
11.plot: In Tempe, Arizona, millionaire entrepreneur Rick Chance is brutally gunned down in a hotel room. The senseless murder leaves his family heartbroken. To catch the killer, detectives turn to their most reliable witness -- surveillance video.

12.title: Someone to Watch Over Her
12.plot: On a freezing winter night, a hardworking mother doesn't make it home from work. As dawn breaks, her body is found in a churchyard. With the city in panic, Police turn to the city's surveillance cameras... hoping they can help catch a brutal murderer.

13.title: Blood Bath
13.plot: A Mother is brutally Murdered in her home. Her twin Daughters are distraught. Or are they?

1.title: Captured on Camera
1.plot: A Philadelphia woman is abducted after getting off a bus on returning home from a friend's party around 10 pm. The police respond to a 911 call from a concerned citizen who heard her screams and pursue the investigation using CCTV footage.

2.title: Last Look of Summer
2.plot: When a young woman is found dead in a Texas landfill, detectives race to discover the killer behind the brutal crime. With no leads, police turn to their only witnesses: video cameras that captured the murderer's chilling attempt to cover his tracks.

3.title: All Eyes on Megan
3.plot: When a teenager goes missing from her local Walmart, detectives struggle for leads. But then surveillance cameras reveal terrifying footage of a prowler kidnapping her, transforming this investigation into a desperate race to bring her home alive.

4.title: Vanished at Noon
4.plot: On November 26th, 2014, Jessica Padgett disappears. The only lead is her abandoned white Subaru. Surveillance cameras show her driving into a parking lot and walking down a back alley, never to return. Will police discover what really happened to her?

5.title: On Her Watch
5.plot: On March 18th, 2011, 32-year-old Patty Ayala is murdered at the Burger King where she works. Police find an open safe and a mysterious message next to her body.

7.title: Dead on Reflection
7.plot: Kimberly Robertson's battered body is found on a sidewalk after a date with her boyfriend. A network of surveillance cameras plays out Kimberly's last few hours alive. Can CCTV footage help catch her killer?

8.title: The Doctor Will See You
8.plot: Closed circuit television reveals images of an unidentified man who left Dr. David Cornbleet in his office bound and gagged in a pool of blood for his daughter to find.

9.title: Eye in the Sky
9.plot: When 27-year-old Christie Wilson disappears after a night at the local casino, surveillance cameras reveal her gambling with a mysterious man. Can this video footage unlock the secrets of what happened next and help bring her home alive?

10.title: Nathan Trapuzzano
10.plot: On April 1, 2014, Indianapolis,IN, Nathan Trappuzano has been shot dead during a morning walk. Police use a tire store's cameras to track his killer and find two suspicious men following him.

12.title: Watch Me Disappear
12.plot: Sian O'Callaghan disappears after a night out in Swindon. The clock ticking, Detectives pull hours of surveillance footage from the area - until they hit gold: footage of her getting into a taxi. Now race is on to ID the vehicle and driver.

13.title: Random Sighting
13.plot: Tosha Lampkin is in Shreveport, Louisiana visiting family. After a late-night trip for food, Tosha disappears. Her burnt out rental car is discovered... along with Tosha's remains. CCTV cameras provide detectives with their only lead on her killers.

1.title: All Eyes on Jordie
1.plot: In 2016, Jordie Hudson vanishes after a night out with friends. The only clue police have is her glasses, which are discovered in a pool of blood. Surveillance footage shows a horrific attack. Can police find her abductor before it's too late?

2.title: Seen at Susan's
2.plot: On April 12th 2008, Susan Casey vanishes after a night out. The only clues left behind are suspicious drag marks outside her home. CCTV footage reveals three different suspects on the scene. Which one is lying and who can tell police where Susan Casey is?

3.title: Stalking Cynthia
3.plot: Cynthia Langrall is shot dead during her morning jog through the normally peaceful Hillcrest Ranch neighborhood in Glendale, Arizona. Home surveillance footage enables detectives to identify the shooter's vehicle but will it be enough to catch the killer?

4.title: At Michelle's Door
4.plot: A woman's New Year's disappearance leads to a gruesome discovery; with no witnesses, only the four security cameras from her apartment building can help decipher what happened.

5.title: Dead Man Walking
5.plot: On September 17th 2015, Edward Lowry is found savagely beaten and stabbed to death in a parking lot in South Dakota. With little evidence left behind at the scene, the police attempt to piece together Ed's last moments from CCTV.

6.title: Beth's Last Party
6.plot: On December 23rd 2009, Beth von Steinner goes missing. Days later, her frozen body is found in a trash pile behind her house. With no witness or suspects, only CCTV footage can unlock the mystery of who killed her.

7.title: Maurice Byrd
7.plot: In Guthrie, OK, 60 year old, social worker, Maurice Byrd has been found shot dead in his own home. Detectives find a church with surveillance cameras right next to Maurice's house to find his killer.

8.title: The Long Night Out
8.plot: Dalene Carlson goes missing after a night out at a bar. Detectives use CCTV to try to find Dalene before it is too late.

9.title: Loretta's Last Valentine
9.plot: On February 14th 2014, pregnant college student Loretta Saunders vanishes without trace. Her trail runs cold after she is spotted on CCTV at her apartment building. The race is now on to find her before it's too late.

10.title: No Good Deed
10.plot: When Diane Cunningham is murdered on September 28, 2014, investigators could find very few clues until security footage reveals a prime suspect.

11.title: Right Man, Wrong Man
11.plot: On June 12th 2013, 46-year-old family man Richard Arenas is gunned down in broad daylight in the driveway of his suburban home in Rhode Island. With no apparent motive or witnesses can investigators track down this cold-hearted killer on CCTV?

12.title: Don't Get in the Truck
12.plot: When Emily Lambert of Garland, Texas goes missing after a night out at a bar with her boyfriend, She was later found murdered in Carlsbad, New Mexico and its up to detectives to sift through security footage to find the truth.

13.title: Shadow of Hope
13.plot: Hope Melton has been kidnapped by an unknown pedestrian. At a gas station, police find CCTV and see a suspicious orange Chevy following Hope.

14.title: Kidnapped at Christmas
14.plot: On Dec 2, 2014 Rhonda Daugherty vanishes; detectives turn to the public for information on her mysterious disappearance, a tip leads investigators to surveillance footage from a hotel where they uncover a journey of duplicity and deception.

15.title: Captain Freddy
15.plot: On 15th August 2015, police are alerted to the body of 70-year-old Fernando Silva on a boat at Warwick Cove, Rhode Island. With the crime scene revealing little about what caused his death, police turn to surveillance footage for clues. Cameras along the cove help them to determine the boat's last movements and a time-line, ultimately leading them to the jetty where Fernando would dock his boat. Will the cameras there help them find out what really happened to Fernando Silva?

16.title: Maple Batalia
16.plot: In Surrey, Canada, actress and college student Maple Batalia has been shot and slashed in the head. Police uses hundreds of surveillance video to find Maple's killer.

-1.title: Right Man, Wrong Man
-1.plot: Family man Richard Arenas is gunned down in broad daylight in the driveway of his suburban home; with no apparent motive or witnesses, investigators watch CCTV footage in an attempt to track down Arenas' cold-hearted killer.

imdb.plot outline: Every second of every day, millions of Americans are caught on CCTV. Most of them are honest citizens going about their everyday lives. But a few are guilty of unspeakable crimes. See no Evil is a ground breaking new series about how real crimes are solved with the help of surveillance cameras. Police reveal how CCTV footage has unlocked the answer to cases that otherwise might have remained unsolved- leaving dangerous killers at large. The series features real footage and dramatic reconstruction, combined with first-hand testimony from police, witnesses, and families.

synopsis:
See No Evil is a new show about how real crimes are solved thanks to security cameras. This show contains real live footage of the crimes and DRAMATIC RECONSTRUCTION combined with confessions from the witnesses, police, and the families.
This new series contains a different murder and case every episode. So far there is currently 6 episodes for season 1. It is currently airing on Slice Tv and will be airing on Investigation Discovery in December of 2014. Further seasons is still unknown as this is a brand new series.
